[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_major"]
[Student "S"]
{NORTH has 14 points so he opens one of his 5-card Major suit, 1\S.

SOUTH has some good \Cs, but with four of partner's Major she doesn't bother bidding anything else. 
Since she has 11 points she jumps to 3\S, a Limit Raise.

NORTH is very close to passing. He now gets to add a point for his doubleton \C which takes 
him up to 15 points. So he has enough to bid 4\S.}

